# Optional seed knowledge DB location.
#
# Neuron ships WITHOUT a seed (empty base knowledge) - it works fine without one.
# To ship a seed, place a valid `base_knowledge.db` here and it will be bundled
# into the wheel (pyproject: package-data neuron = ["data/*.db"]) and loaded at
# runtime by neuron.registry.GraphRegistry via importlib.resources.
#
# Build one from your own notes/docs:
#     set NEURON_VAULT=C:\path\to\your\notes
#     python scripts/import_vault.py
# Then copy the generated .db here only if you deliberately want it shipped.
#
# IMPORTANT: never commit a truncated/placeholder .db here. The loader guards
# against it (must be a real SQLite file >= 512 bytes), but a corrupt seed used
# to crash vector search with "short read on page 1". See README / DEVELOPER.md.
